ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: 1. Do you dislike the physical sensation you get when people hug you?
2. Do you gag when you are eating certain foods, perhaps feeling as if you are going to be sick?
3. Do you find it difficult to manipulate your hands when completing a delicate task?
4. Do you ever run your hand around the outside of an object before picking it up?
5. Do you stand very close or very far when you are talking to someone?
6. Do you find certain noises/pitches of sound annoying?
7. Do you smell your food before you eat it?
8. Do bright lights ever hurt your eyes/cause a headache?
9. Do you like to listen to the same piece of music/part of a DVD over and over again?
10. Do you feel ill/dizzy/peculiar if you have to reach up high or bend down low for something?
11. Do you find yourself fascinated by small particles?
12. Do you like to spin yourself round and round?
13. Do you ever feel ill just from smelling a certain odour?
14. Do you find it difficult to hear what people are saying?
15. Do you dislike having a haircut?
16. Do you notice that you have hurt yourself but did not feel any pain?
17. Are you ever told by others that you wear too much perfume/after-shave?
18. Do lights ever seem to flicker when you look at them?
19. Do you like lining objects up?
20. Do you rock yourself backwards and forwards?
21. Do you find it difficult to go into a strong-smelling shop?
22. Do you cut the labels out of your clothes?
23. Do you hate the feel or texture of certain foods in your mouth?
24. Do you avoid going to restaurants because you can smell a certain odour?
25. Do you dislike loud noises?
26. Do you use the tip of your tongue to taste your food before eating it?
27. Does your body ever feel numb -  like you can't feel anything against your skin?
28. Do you think you have a weak sense of taste?
29. Do you find that you are unaware of your body's signals?
30. Do you ever feel dizzy/ill when playing fast-paced sports?
31. Do you react very strongly when you hear an unexpected sound?
32. Do you dislike walking on uneven surfaces?
33. Do you really like listening to certain sounds?
34. Do you like to run about - perhaps up and down in straight lines or round in circles?
35. Do you chew and lick objects that aren't food because you like the way they feel in your mouth?
36. Do you enjoy wearing very strong perfumes/after-shaves?
37. Do you find that you position your body in a way that is different to most people?
38. Do you find it difficult to tie your shoelaces or button up your clothes?
39. Do you find that you are able to go outside without a coat or jacket when other people think that it is too cold?
40. Do you eat the same foods most of the time?
41. Do you like to wear something/hold something so that you know where your body ends?
42. Do you flick your fingers in front of your eyes?
